The paper deals with the convergence of different grammars of the same language, which is a topic related to programming languages (cs.PL) and software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also describes a refined method for grammar convergence, which involves the use of transformation-based representation and operator suite, which are topics related to machine learning (cs.LG) and computational linguistics (cs.CL). Finally, the paper involves the extraction of metadata and the use of automated processing, which are topics related to scientific computing (cs.SC).
